heaviest_rainfall.status: Ranked 7th for total rainfall, today's storm had precipitation totalling 23.15mm, falling at 8.3mm per hour at times during the 30.2 hour long storm.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 7th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 30.2 hours; it delivered 23.15mm of rain at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 24.6mm per hour.
